    <h1>Contact AIMS Travel</h1>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Archived Site Notice</h3>
      <p>
        This is an archival website. AIMS Travel is no longer actively operating tours or accepting bookings. The information on this site is preserved as a historical reference. If you are looking for a current international group tour operator, we recommend searching for active operators that serve your destination of interest. Organizations such as the United States Tour Operators Association (USTOA) and the American Society of Travel Advisors (ASTA) maintain directories of vetted tour operators and travel agencies.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Planning International Group Travel</h2>
    <p>
      If you are researching international group travel for the first time, or looking to find a new operator after traveling with AIMS Travel in the past, here are some practical considerations when evaluating your options:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Verify operator credentials.</strong> Look for membership in recognized industry associations such as USTOA or ASTA. These organizations require members to meet financial and professional standards and maintain consumer protection programs.</li>
      <li><strong>Ask about group size.</strong> Smaller groups (typically under 25 travelers) generally allow for a more personalized experience, greater flexibility with local logistics, and easier access to smaller venues and restaurants.</li>
      <li><strong>Review the itinerary depth.</strong> A well-constructed itinerary will balance major landmarks with less-visited cultural sites, include free time for independent exploration, and provide context through knowledgeable guides rather than simply moving travelers from point to point.</li>
      <li><strong>Confirm what is included.</strong> All-inclusive pricing — covering flights, accommodations, guided excursions, and most meals — makes budgeting easier and reduces the risk of unexpected costs. Ask specifically about internal flights, tips, and optional excursions.</li>
      <li><strong>Check dietary and cultural accommodations.</strong> Reputable operators can accommodate a range of dietary requirements and cultural preferences, including kosher, halal, vegetarian, and allergy-specific meal needs. Confirm this before booking if it applies to your travel party.</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top:2rem"><a href="/destinations">Browse destinations &rarr;</a> &nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href="/">Back to home &rarr;</a></p>
  </main>
